      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Get or set a speech channelâ€™s pitch modulation.The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "speechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter isa pointer to a variable of type ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Fixed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".Pitch modulation is also expressed as a fixed-point value in therange of 0.000 to 127.000. These values correspond to MIDI notevalues, where 60.000 is equal to middle C on a piano scale. Themost useful speech pitches fall in the range of 40.000 to 55.000.A pitch modulation value of 0.000 corresponds to a monotone in whichall speech is generated at the frequency corresponding to the speech pitch.Given a speech pitch value of 46.000, a pitch modulation of 2.000 wouldmean that the widest possible range of pitches corresponding tothe actual frequency of generated text would be 44.000 to 48.000.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This selector works with both the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The change in pitch modulation may not be noticeable until the next sentence or paragraph is spoken.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
